       These are the Window Class specific attributes.

       You may set these while the window is @{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500} open, at @{"NewObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/NewObject"}
       time or @{"SetAttrs()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/SetAttrsA"} - between @{"WM_CLOSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/window_cl/WM_CLOSE"} and @{"WM_OPEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/window_cl/WM_OPEN"} for example.

       @{"WINDOW_Position" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 86} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
           Set the intial opening position of the window.
           See Also, @{"WINDOW_RefWindow" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 133}.

               @{"WPOS_CENTERSCREEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 231} - Center in visible screen clip.
               @{"WPOS_CENTERMOUSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 232}  - Center under mouse.
               @{"WPOS_TOPLEFT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 233}      - Open Top/Left, just below screen bar.
               @{"WPOS_CENTERWINDOW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 234} - Center in some other window.
               @{"WPOS_FULLSCREEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 235}   - Open Top/Left, and fill the screen clip.

           If @{"WINDOW_RefWindow" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 133} is set, @{"WPOS_CENTERSCREEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 231} will center
           in the refwindow, not the screen. As of 42.42, @{"WPOS_FULLSCREEN" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 235}
           remains broken, window will open a minimum size.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_LockWidth" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 73} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})
           If @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, lock the width of the window, ie, disallow
           resizing in this orientation.

           Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_LockHeight" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 77} (@{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52})
           If @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, lock the height of the window, ie, disallow
           resizing in this orientation.

           Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_SharedPort" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 54} (@{"struct MsgPort" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/ports.h/File" 28} *)
           Pointer to a custom UserPort this window should share.

           Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

       @{"WINDOW_AppPort" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 81} (@{"struct MsgPort" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/ports.h/File" 28} *)
           Pointer to a MsgPort this window should use for AppMessages.
           By passing this tag the window turns into an AppWindow and
           you can use the @{"WM_ICONIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/window_cl/WM_ICONIFY"} method. WindowClass must use the
           ID field of the AppMessages to identify the window to which
           the message was intended. You can use the UserData field
           yourself.

           Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_AppWindow" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 116} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
           By providing an AppPort and setting this to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95}, the window
           will be made a Workbench AppWindow. If you don't set this
           attribute, the AppPort will only be used to support
           iconification.

           Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_IconifyGadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 122} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
           Set to @{"TRUE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 95} to add an iconification gadget to the window
           titlebar. Please note that currently windowclass detects
           the iconify gadget being pressed by using the gadget ID
           0xfffe.  Do not use this ID in your application.

           Defaults to @{"FALSE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 98}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_BackFillName" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 128} (@{"STRPTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 67})
           Name for the custom backfill to use instead of global CAPrefs
           backfill. If you use this tag, make it a user preference.

           Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})


       It is legal and safe to set any of these at any time, @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63} or
       @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65} regardless of of the window being open or not, if
       not applicable, the setting will be ignored.

       @{"WA_BusyPointer" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1350} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
           Set the window to a busy state. It will set busy pointer
           on the window. Setting the busy state will also clear the
           DeferLayout state, clearing the busy state restores the
           DeferLayout state to its last value.

           This is done since, its a logical assumption if the application
           is busy enough that a pointer change is waranted, then its
           probably busy to respond to defer requests in a timely fashion.

           Note, the window put to sleep creating a @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} requester.
           In prior versions of window class before V42.40, the layout
           group was set to readonly, and menu strip removed.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_Layout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 43} (Object *)
       @{"WINDOW_ParentLayout" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 44}
       @{"WINDOW_ParentGroup" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 45}
           Pointer to the parent level layout group object which
           will be added to the window.

           Note the tag has 2 aliased definitions which are now
           obsolete but still supported in the include files.

           Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_Zoom" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 60} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
           Cause the window to to be zipped via @{"ZipWindow()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/ZipWindow"}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_FrontBack" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 63} (@{"BOOL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 91})
           Changes window depth arrangement via @{"WindowToFront()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/WindowToFront"} or
           @{"WindowToBack()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/WindowToBack"}. Accepted settings;

               @{"WT_FRONT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 226} - bring window to front.
               @{"WT_BACK" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 227}  - put window to back

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_UserData" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 49} (@{"APTR" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 49})
           Pointer to your user data. Take note, this is *@{"NOT" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 1500}* the
           same pointer as the Intuition Window's UserData.

           Defaults to @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_GET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 66})

       @{"WINDOW_GadgetUserData" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 95} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
           Determines how a gadget's UserData should be interpreted.
           If the userdata is non-null, and this setting is not
           @{"WGUD_IGNORE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 105}, then the (hook) function will be called
           when the gadget is selected.

           A function gets the hook's "object" argument in a0 and the
           "message" argument in a1.

           Possible values are;

               @{"WGUD_HOOK" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 103}   - UserData is hook pointer (@{"struct Hook" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/utility/hooks.h/File" 28} *).
               @{"WGUD_FUNC" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 104}   - UserData is a pointer to function.
               @{"WGUD_IGNORE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 105} - Ignore UserData.

           Defaults to @{"WGUD_IGNORE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 105}.

           Applicability is (@{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65})

       @{"WINDOW_MenuUserData" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 100} (@{"UWORD" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 55})
           Like the @{"WINDOW_GadgetUserData" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 95} tag, but for menus. Using
           this implies that @{"WINDOW_MenuStrip" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/classes/window.h/File" 37} has been created with
